  "body": "\n***Type***: Bug\n\n***Summary***: It was noticed with 2G connection (on iOS), where network to receive/send data is really poor. Also, perfectly reproducible if you don't have any funds on SIM so no cellular data available and any of LTE/3G/2G networks are enabled.\nWhen using Status app with above conditions - app freezes when navigating between the screens.\nIn the video below pay attention at:  23rd, 37th, 59th seconds - at that point app was freezing  https://drive.google.com/file/d/1zQ1MZPiH25ioNjSL6iB9yTnUsyGlwT7-/view?usp=sharing\n\nNOTE: issue with app freezing is not present when Airplane mode enabled \nNOTE2: it's all fine with 3G/LTE cellular data enabled.\n\n#### Expected behavior\nNo freezes when poor (2G) / limited (3G/LTE enabled but no access to cellular data) connection is enabled.\n \n#### Actual behavior\nStatus app freezes when using it while poor 2G connection enabled [iOS]\n\n### Preconditions\nWiFi disabled. \n2G cellular enabled (OR your SIM card does not have funds)\n\n### Reproduction\n\n- Open Status \n- Create new account\n- Join public chat \n\n### Additional Information\n* Status version: 0.10.1, Develop 0.11.0\n* Operating System: iOS 12.1.4 (iPhoneX)",
